task.summary: Default task

test fixes
Final test fixes excluding 2 last ones inside testLilypondRun which need a bit of moving around of directions to get right.

issue fix #47, directions wot wrap
directions that wrap the bar are now added to the measure item itself, rather than the tree structure: currently just Brackets that add to the item, if any more need adding simply add the instance type to the wrappers list inside addDirections

proper implementation of voices mentioned in issue #42
Updated voice implementation so that it is now implemented on note, measure and direction level: had to refactor the getMeasure method slightly so that it gets the child directly from the stave as opposed to searching for it because it was confusing the system where a voice and measure id were the same (this is an underlying bug, but the search methods aren't all that useful on this level anyway so it's not necessary to fix it unless I really need it later on)

work towards issue #51
Modified how divisions are set: underlying issue was that staves aren't all known at the point of measure being created (tho could use the "staves" tag to implement this) so it now does a check at the end of measure tag. However, "r0" is still appearing in violin score of ActorPreludeSample so not entirely fixed yet.

issue fix #51
Fixed issue by resetting staff and voice variables to 1 at the end of every measure. Should be no more failures on durations coming out funny, but lilypond still falling over on bar checks so needs more checking

issue fix #52
Handling time sigs properly now but still need a new test for it.

issue fix #53
Replaced any rest measures with the appropriate notation of "R1". This has made ActorPreludeSample a lot less crushed in, but there's still some compression happening and a few bar checks are still failing.

issue fix #39
Implemented dotted notes as lilypond was falling over because of bar checks because they weren't being handled. Also had to adjust according to whether the note was in a chord or not, as with durations on chords. Fixed another bug that I had forgotten about the layer of voices in the MeasureNode meaning that chord types were not being updated at the end of every measure being put in.

work towards issue #55
Modified tree structure so that notes which are of a chord are now added to the previous note. Need to change how this functions in MxmlParser.

work towards issue #55
Fixed a problem in how chords are handled in that the expression addition method was messing things up: it now checks to make sure the first object is a Note, if so put it to the second child etc. Also fixed the title/meta issue whereby title and such wasn't being outputted because SetupPiece was adding everything to PieceNode not Piece item - doesn't make a lot of difference but keeps things clean and means I don't have to move a bunch of code over.

work towards issue #56
Added a new method at measure item level which calculates the maximum value in lilypond notation a bar can have for use when a measure is a rest measure. This is called at measure node level when it's "rest" value is set to true, done when a measureRest note is encountered. It will then pass in the value to voice which uses it to figure out what notation to write - this skips out the note's notation entirely: at present this also skips any directions or expressions, tho thinking I should change that as even though expressions are likely to not appear, directions like text markings could still appear. Still not perfect: if a bar does not have a meter but is a rest measure, it will fail, so we need to have a method which calls this and applies it to future methods unless they have their own meter.

issue fix #56
Added a method which goes through each bar checking it's total value and setting it if it can't calculate it from it's own meter. Also added a method which does a check at the end of every measure to make sure time sig is set per-stave, like the Divisions check I previously implemented. Final testcase ActorPreludeSample shows all bars now, but will need some scaling and spacing options setting in lilypond.

added further try excepts around the last few import statements so that script can now run from terminal or pycharm. This needs cleaning up at some point so that we change working directory to the level above classes folder, but for now it works ok. Also confirmed that rendering method works on a random file from musescore and everything except the credit text works just fine.

issue fix #32 slurs
slurs are now properly handled and outputted to lilypond. Need to add a testcase for slurs and ties
issue fix #57

issue fix #82
Fixed the problem by changing where credit text gets added: if it is right aligned, it gets added to "composer" attrib. center goes to title and bottom goes to copyright.

issue fix #81
Problem was in fact that for some reason, the testcase I was applying this to made the parser load the title in in chunks: every time a new chunk was added it would replace the old one, and as the end of the tag had not been hit it would never have an effect on the title of the piece. Fixed this by appending text to the value where the tag is already in the chars dictionary.

issue fix #80
Lilypond has this in place already - called "instrumentShortName" so fix was very simple

work towards issue #83
Added handler for partgroups and the infrastructure inside piece node. Need to puzzle out how best to go forward inside lily method

issue fix #83 part groups
This fix has slown down lilypond quite a lot for some reason? Anyway groups are now put into the system and any parts which are in a group are excluded from the second for loop, meaning it won't accidentally get shown twice

issue fix #84 chord beams
Fixed problem where notes which are part of a chord were not displaying beam issues properly because the last note of the chord didn't have the right beam information. Solved by copying them down when a chord note is added

working toward issue #97
Added a method which checks for tab clef upon closure of a method. If it finds it, it throws an exception because tab notation isn't something I want to handle at the present moment in time.

work towards issue #97
tab output seems to be getting sent to lilypond, but lilypond ignores it unless we're in a TabStaff. Vetoing tab notation anyway so it doesn't make a deal of a difference, but will try and cover drum tab while I'm here so going to update the tab checker method to check both.

issue fix #97

made a bunch of changes that probably aren't actually helpful to development. Current work is toward issue #98 - trying another caching system which sits and waits for a voice ID rather than adding with the last one we found.
temporarily got rid of the cache system 'cause it doesn't work and my brain is exploding thinking about it. Will go look at something else for a while.

work towards issue #94
Put in a new method which handles the calculation of transposition lilystrings and added some tests to confirm it's behaviour

work towards issue #94
Added a check at staff level which closes transposition braces. Added another 2 tests to check how this works

work towards issue #94
Further changes and attempted running against a transposing instrument score: failed

work towards issue #94
Actually looked at the scores again and this doesn't need to be applied, but we do need to find a way to force lilypond to take the note and apply the sharps or flats of the appropriate keysignature rather than sharpen or neutralise them when it encounters say a c# as a c

issue fix #100
Problem with sharps and flats appearing as naturals was actually that the alter tag was being loaded as a string, not an int, and therefore wasn't "in" the alter dictionary within the pitch item. added a cast around the alter tag as it gets loaded in and the testcase now passes, although we need to ensure children are processed in order in the PieceNode toLily method as currently their keys could come in any order.

testcase fix for issue #97
Percussion clef now works in clef testcase. Tab clef still not able to get working from inside a regular staff, so will ignore that bar. Moving clef testcase to passing testcases

issue fix #103
Instrument names are now markups rather than just strings, and columns and lines for each are handled properly

quick bug fix to issue #103
Fixed a bug whereby lilyrenderer would throw an exception if there were no /rs or /ns in a part string. Also removed quotation marks and # symbol where name is set in a staffGroup which was causing lilypond to fall over.

added a hacky fix to the wrapping problem - notation that is a wrapper now returns a list, notation that is not returns a string. will not work with 2 layered-directions, though.
